=head Name, Registration, and Business Language

=numitem Name

The foundation bears the name of: The A<FDN>.

=numitem Registration

The foundation has its registered office in A<RegPlace>.

=numitem Business Language

All documents related to the A<FDN> shall be in English, except for those required by
the laws of the Netherlands and those required for companies registered in the Netherlands
which shall be in the language or languages required by the laws of the Netherlands or
the regulations covering registration in the Netherlands.

=head Object
=numitem

The object of the A<FDN> is:
=item to promote and support the use of A<RP> globally,
=item to be an authority to determine the quality of software written in A<RP>,
=item to organise conferences, seminars, workshops and other events to further A<FDN>'s other objectives,
=item to coordinate with educational institutions to further A<FDN>'s other objectives,
=item to provide consulting and managerial support concerning A<RP> to individuals and other organisations,
=item to facilitate and manage projects that develop software written in or supporting A<RP>,
=item to encourage other individuals and organisations, including for-profit companies to undertake projects that create or use software written in whole in part in A<RP>,
=item to do everything that is directly or indirectly connected with or can be beneficial to the above, all of this in the widest sense of the word.

=head Finance
=numitem Revenues

The A<FDN> gets its revenue from:
=item subsidies and donations,
=item gifts, testamentary dispositions, grants and specific legacies,
=item membership fees,
=item consulting and management fees paid by third parties,
=item profit from the operation of the A<FDN>,
=item all other acquisitions and revenues.

=numitem Reserves and Operating Budget
=item The A<FDN> shall create an operating budget from which its monthly expenses will be paid, on an accrual basis.
=item The A<FDN> shall create unrestricted reserves, into which revenues from for-profit organisations will be paid.
=item The A<FDN> shall create restricted reserves, into which will be paid grants for projects, donations, subsidies, gifts, grants and legacies and the like, which may have covenants or conditions about the use to which the monies may be expended.
=item The operating budget may be formed from current revenues from membership fees, consulting and management fees, donations from individuals, interest paid on reserves and investments, and profits from the operation of the A<FDN>.
=item The operating budget may be augmented by transfers from its unrestricted reserves with the provision that no more than A<RevConst> of the monthly operating budget averaged over the preceeding A<RunMonth> months may come from an unrestricted reserve formed from revenues originating from a single for-profit organisation.


=head Governance
=numitem Overview

The A<FDN> shall be governed by three governing bodies, namely
=item its A<Exec>,
=item its A<Super>,
=item and its A<Mem>

The A<FDN>, its governing bodies, the membership of the governing bodies as individuals, and its agents shall operate according to these Articles of Association, and to the A<FDN>'s Regulations.

=numitem Regulations

A list of the A<FDN>'s Regulations is appended to these Articles of Association.

The A<Exec> shall implement and enforce the Regulations, except where the enforcement of a Regulation breaches the laws of a country in which the effect of enforcement occurs.

=numitem Decision types

Actions affecting the existence, operation, or reputation of A<FDN> in any way to be undertaken, executed, set in motion by any officers of the A<FDN> or any of its agents shall be assigned to one of the following categories
=item Operational
=item Important
=item Critical

=numitem Determination of the type of an action

The category of an action may be specified in these Articles of Association, or in the Regulations, or by a majority of the A<Exec>.

=numitem Consent for actions

Before an action as defined in Article 'Decision types' is undertaken, executed or set in motion, the action must be formulated into a proposal that is voted on by the A<FDN>'s executive bodies. The proposal is deemed to have received consent if a majority of a quorum of the voters are in favour of the proposal.

=numitem Consent for Operational action

It is sufficient for a majority of the A<Exec>'s members with a quorum of three to vote in favour of a proposal for an Operation action to receive consent.

=numitem Consent for an Important action

It is sufficient for a majority of the A<Exec>'s members with a quorum of three, and a majority of the A<Super> with a quorum of twenty-five percent of its living members to vote in favour of a proposal for an Important action to receive consent.

=numitem Consent for an Critical action

It is sufficient for a majority of the A<Exec>'s members with a quorum of three, and a majority of the A<Super> with a quorum of forty percent of its living members, and a majority of the A<Mem> with a quorum of twenty percent of the total membership to vote in favour of a proposal for a Critical action to receive consent.

=head The A<Exec>

=numitem Number of members

The A<Exec> shall consist of an uneven number of members, as defined in the Regulations, provided that the number is no less than three and no more than 19.

=numitem Process of election

The A<Exec> shall be elected each year by the A<Mem> as follows:
=item The A<Exec> shall draw up a list of the current membership with the right to vote; and shall determine the deadline for the ballots to be received, which should be a working day in A<RegPlace>, on or close to the 21st of March.
=item A communication shall be sent as defined by the Regulations to all the members of the A<Mem> no later than the last working day in A<RegPlace> before the 21st of January requesting each member to become a Candidate for election to the A<Exec>. No nomination process or qualification is needed, other than a willingness to serve as a member of the A<Exec> for a year.
=item A communication shall be sent as defined by the Regulations to all the members of the A<Mem> no later than the last working day before 21st February, informing the membership of the upcoming election, the method of the election, the deadline for the receipt of ballots, and a list of the Candidates for election to the A<Mem>.
=item Each member of the A<Mem> is encouraged to send in a ballot using the process described in the Regulations.
=item At the close of business in A<RegPlace> on the day of the deadline, the votes shall be counted as defined below, and the Candidates receiving the most votes, as defined below, shall be considered the members of the A<Exec>, starting from 21 April.
=item The members of the A<Exec> shall serve from 21 April in one year to 20 April in the next year.

=numitem Counting of votes

All of the ballots from members received on or before the day of the deadline shall checked for valid votes as follows:
=item Each ballot sent in by a member shall consist of the number of names selected from the list of Candidates as the Regulations specify for the number of A<Exec> members.
=item In the event of a duplicated Candidate name, only one shall be considered valid, and the duplicates shall be invalidated.
=item In the event of name recorded in a ballot not on the list of Candidates, that name shall be invalidated.
=item In the event of more than the specifed number of valid Candidate names, the first names to the specified number shall be considered valid and the remainder shall be invalidated.

The valid votes cast for each Candidate shall be counted, with each valid vote considered equal without reference to its position on the list.

=numitem Determination of A<Exec> members

The Candidates upto the number of members of the A<Exec> with the most votes shall be declared members of the A<Exec> from the following 21st April.

In the event that more Candidates have the top positions than there are A<Exec> members specified in the Regulations because two or more Candidates have the same number of votes, then one or more Candidates shall be drawn at random from the group of Candiates sharing the same number of votes until the number of A<Exec> members as specified in the Regulations is chosen.

=numitem Vacancy on A<Exec>

The number of members of the A<Exec> may fall beneath the number defined in the Regulations because a member of the A<Exec>
=item dies or is rendered incapable by disease or accident;
=item resigns in writing (retires);
=item loses the right to dispose of their property;
=item is removed by the court, pursuant to Article 2.298 of the Netherlands Civil Code.

A member of the A<Exec> may be removed as a result of an Important Action.

=numitem A<Exec> remuneration

The members of the A<Exec> shall not be paid a remuneration for their activities.  However, in so far as the assets of the A<FDN> allow for this, they have a right to compensation for the expenses incurred by them in the performances of their duties.

