=head Change of, Addition to or Amendment of The Articles of Association
=numitem The Articles of Association may be changed, added to or ammended as a result of an Critical Action
=numitem The proposal for such an action may be made by any member of the A<FDN>

=head Change of, Addition to or Amendment of Regulations
=numitem The Regulations may be changed, added to or ammended as a result of an Important Action
=numitem The proposal for such an action may be made by any member of the A<FDN>
=numitem The A<Exec> is obliged to file a copy of the deed of amendment, as well as the amended articles of association at the office of the Trade Register held by the authorized Chamber of Commerce and Industry appointed by law.


=head Financial year and annual report and accounts
=numitem Period

The financial year of the A<FDN> is the same as the calendar year.

=numitem Records

The A<Exec> is obliged to keep records of the financial condition of the A<FDN>, in accordance with the requirements arising from these activities, in such a manner and to keep the books, documents, correspondence, computer files and other data carriers pertaining thereto in such a manner that the assets, the rights and obligations of the A<FDN> can be inspected at all times.

=numitem Financial reports

Without prejudice to what is provided otherwise by law, the A<Exec> is obliged to prepare and put on paper the balance sheet and the statement of income and expenditure of the A<FDN> each year within six months after the end of the financial year.  In the event that the A<FDN> maintains one or more enterprises, which, pursuant to the law, have to be listed in the Trade Register of the Chamber of Commerce, the net turnover and profit or loss of each enterprise shall be stated in the statement of income and expenditure.

=numitem Archiving

The A<Exec> is obliged to keep the books, documents, correspondence, computer files and other data carriers referred to in Article 'Financial reports' and Article 'Records' for seven years.

The data stored on a data carrier, with the exception of the balance sheet and statement of income and expenditure that have been put on paper, can be transferred to and kept on another data carrier, provided that the transfer takes place with correct and complete representation of the data and that these data will be available throughout the time they have to be retained and will always be legible.

=head Dissolution and Liquidation
=numitem

The A<FDN> shall be dissolved as the result of a Critical Action

After its dissolution the A<FDN> shall continue to exist in so far as is necessary for the liquidation of its assets.

The liquidation shall be carried out by the A<Exec>.

The A<Exec> shall see to it that the dissolution of the A<FDN> be listed in the Trade Register of the Chamber of Commerce.

During the liquidation, the provisions of these articles of association shall remain in force as much as possible.

Any liquidation surplus of the dissolved A<FDN> shall as much as possible be spent in accordance with the object of the A<FDN>.  Resolutions thereto shall be adopted unanimously.

At the end of the liquidation the books, accounts, documents and other data carriers of the dissolved A<FDN> shall be in the custody of the liquidator appointed by the A<Exec> for seven years, thereby ensuring safety, legibility and usability.

